Package com.cyc.baseclient.subl.subtypes

Java representations of general types of SubL functions and variables.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractSubLMultiArgFunction<T,V>
    Extends BasicSubLFunction to provide support methods for evaluating the function with multiple arguments.
    AbstractSubLNoArgFunction<V>
    Extends BasicSubLFunction to provide support methods for evaluating the function with no arguments.
    AbstractSubLSingleArgFunction<T,V>
    Extends BasicSubLFunction to provide support methods for evaluating the function with a single argument.
    BasicSubLFunction
    Provides a basic, common implementation of SubLFunction.
    BasicSubLGlobalVariable<T>
    Provides a basic, common implementation of SubLGlobalVariable.
    SubLBooleanNoArgFunction
    A representation of a SubL function which takes no arguments and returns a boolean value.
    SubLBooleanSingleArgFunction<T>
    A representation of a SubL function which takes a single argument and returns a boolean value.
    SubLCycListNoArgFunction<E>
    A representation of a SubL function which takes no arguments and returns a CycList.
    SubLCycObjectNoArgFunction
    A representation of a SubL function which takes no arguments and returns a CycObject.
    SubLCycObjectSingleArgFunction<T>
    A representation of a SubL function which takes a single argument and returns a CycObject.
    SubLStringNoArgFunction
    A representation of a SubL function which takes no arguments and returns a String.
    SubLStringSingleArgFunction<T>
    A representation of a SubL function which takes a single argument and returns a String.

Package com.cyc.baseclient.subl.subtypes Description

Java representations of general types of SubL functions and variables. Many of the classes in com.cyc.baseclient.subl.functions which represent specific functions are built on these general types.
